webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Valdemarsvik from above 1933. At the time of the picture, the settlement was even highly concentrated in the valley towards Valdemarsviken. The long distance to the parish Ringarum forced its own church in the 1870s. It was completed in 1877, erected after drawings by architect Axel Lindegren. The tower came to 1905. The dominant industry in picture is Lundberg’s leather factory - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000084. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419435. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
